# Supabase Data Provider

## Access pattern

- Get clients only from `SupabaseProvider.browser()` / `SupabaseProvider.server(...)`.
- Configure with `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` + `VITE_SUPABASE_KEY` (publishable key, `sb_publishable_...`).
- All DB/Storage access goes through a `*Repository` extending `BaseRepository`.
- Repositories map DB rows (snake_case) to domain types (camelCase in `src/lib/domain/types.ts`).
- Never leak raw Postgres errors to the client; wrap via `this.fail(...)` (`RepositoryError`).

## Security

- Every table has **RLS enabled and forced**; ownership is scoped through `lines.owner_id`.
- Documents live in a **private** Storage bucket; access is via short-lived **signed URLs** only.
- Storage object paths are `{owner_id}/{line_id}/{event_id}/{filename}` and RLS checks the leading owner segment.
- Keep the migration files (`supabase/migrations/*.sql`) as the source of truth; regenerate types
  with `pnpm db:types` after schema changes.

## Enums

- `event_type` values (`MA`, `O`, `MT`, `S`, `other`) come from `EVENT_TYPE_CODES` (const tuple)
  in `src/lib/domain/event-type.ts` — update that tuple + the SQL enum together.
